<task id="026" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Forward mode — pre-fill with attachment carry + Fwd: prefix + sprk_inreplyto stamp</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 003</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Forward mode carries attachments by default (user can deselect) + stamps thread linkage; user-facing complexity around attachment-deselect-before-send. FULL appropriate.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-12</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `forward` mode behavior in `EmailComposer/modes/forwardMode.ts` (pure logic) + integration in the reducer + send path. Companion to task 025 reply mode; key behavioral difference is ATTACHMENT CARRY.

    Pre-fill behavior (FR-12) — derived from `sourceRecord`:
    - `to` = `[]` (user fills in)
    - `cc` = `[]`
    - `subject`:
      * If `sourceRecord.subject` starts with `/^Fwd:\s*/i` → keep as-is
      * Else → `Fwd: ${sourceRecord.subject}`
    - `body` = wrap original body with a divider (HTML/plaintext variants, similar to reply quoting):
      ```
      ---------- Forwarded message ----------
      From: {sourceRecord.from.displayName}
      Date: {sentDate}
      Subject: {sourceRecord.subject}
      To: {sourceRecord.to.map(r =&gt; r.displayName).join(', ')}

      {sourceRecord.body}
      ```
    - `attachments` = **carried by default**, each pre-checked. User can deselect via AttachmentList row checkbox or remove button. Deselected items removed from request before send.
    - `associations` = `[...sourceRecord.associations]`

    Stamping on send (FR-12):
    - New `sprk_communication.sprk_inreplyto` set to `sourceRecord.communicationId` (same as reply — forward is also a thread continuation)
    - `threadId` carried over from sourceRecord

    AttachmentList carries a "checkbox per row in forward mode" UX twist: in forward mode, each row has a checkbox (instead of just a remove button). Unchecked → not included in send. Sub-component update needed.

    Files:
    - `modes/forwardMode.ts` (NEW) — pure functions
    - Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts` — handle `mode === 'forward'` initialState + transition
    - Update `EmailComposer.tsx` — send-path stamping (same as reply: include `inReplyTo` + `threadId`)
    - Update `AttachmentList.tsx` — add `forwardMode` prop that renders checkbox column; engine filters un-checked attachments before send
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + TypeScript developer familiar with attachment-carry semantics from email clients (Outlook, Gmail Forward UX).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `forward` mode pre-fills correctly per FR-12. Attachments carried + pre-checked + deselectable. Subject prefix dedup. New record stamped with `sprk_inreplyto` + `threadId`. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-12: forward IS in the thread (same `sprk_inreplyto` stamping as reply). The difference vs reply is attachment carry + To/Cc behavior.

      Attachment carry: forwarded attachments use the same `driveItemId` references as the source — no re-upload needed; the BFF resolves the existing SPE driveItems.

      Subject prefix: `Fwd:` is industry standard. Some clients use `FW:` — we standardize on `Fwd:`. The dedup regex catches both: `/^F(wd|w):\s*/i`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/modes/forwardMode.ts (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.reducer.ts (UPDATE)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.tsx (UPDATE)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx (UPDATE — forward-mode checkbox column)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-024">Server-side polymorphic resolver unchanged — client just carries associations</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Forward-mode logic in canonical engine — no parallel forward UI</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Subject dedup: `/^F(wd|w):\s*/i` — handles `Fwd:` and `FW:` variants</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Attachments carried + pre-checked; deselected items filtered before send</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Same `sprk_inreplyto` stamping as reply (per FR-12)</constraint>
  </constraints>

