  <steps>
    <step order="1">Author `modes/forwardMode.ts`:
      - `deriveForwardState(sourceRecord: IComposerSourceRecord): Partial&lt;EmailComposerState&gt;` — pre-fill per FR-12
      - `formatForwardBody(originalBody, bodyFormat, metadata: { fromName, sentDate, subject, toList }): string`
      - Re-use `dedupSubjectPrefix` from replyMode.ts (export from there or move to a shared `modes/util.ts`)</step>
    <step order="2">Update `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`:
      - `initialState` handles `mode === 'forward' &amp;&amp; sourceRecord` by applying `deriveForwardState` — IMPORTANT: each carried attachment gets a `forwardSelected: true` flag (extend `IAttachment` type with `forwardSelected?: boolean` — defaults true)
      - `SET_MODE` from view → forward applies same logic
      - New action: `TOGGLE_ATTACHMENT_SELECTED` for forward-mode deselect</step>
    <step order="3">Update `EmailComposer.tsx` send-path:
      - When `mode === 'forward'`, filter attachments by `forwardSelected !== false` before sending
      - Include `inReplyTo: sourceRecord.communicationId` + `threadId: sourceRecord.threadId` in request</step>
    <step order="4">Update `AttachmentList.tsx`:
      - Add `forwardMode?: boolean` prop
      - When `forwardMode`, render checkbox column for each row; checkbox state from `attachment.forwardSelected`
      - On toggle, dispatch `TOGGLE_ATTACHMENT_SELECTED` via callback</step>
    <step order="5">Update `IAttachment` type in `AttachmentList.types.ts` to add optional `forwardSelected?: boolean`.</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test in dev: load a record with 2 attachments, click Forward, verify subject `Fwd: ${original}`, both attachments pre-checked, deselect one, send → request body has 1 attachment.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="7.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 026 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

