  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Forward pre-fill: `to=[]`, `cc=[]`, `subject` single "Fwd: " prefix, body wrapped with forward header.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All source attachments carried with `forwardSelected: true` default.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Deselected attachments filtered before send.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">On send, request body contains `inReplyTo: sourceRecord.communicationId` + `threadId`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Subject dedup: `Fwd: Fwd: foo` preserved.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Body quoting respects bodyFormat (HTML vs plaintext).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Engine's `IAttachment.forwardSelected` is optional — only meaningful in forward mode. Other modes treat undefined as "included".

    Carried attachments retain their `driveItemId` references — no re-upload. Server (existing R2 path) attaches by driveItemId.
  </notes>

